Assuming the variables "a" and "b" are integers, what will be the value of "c" after executing the following PHP code?
$a = 10;
$b = 5;
$c = $a + $b;
echo $c;

After executing the given PHP code:

```php
$a = 10;
$b = 5;
$c = $a + $b;
echo $c;
```

The value of the variable "c" will be 15. This is because the code adds the values of "a" (10) and "b" (5) and assigns the result (15) to "c". The `echo $c;` statement will then output the value 15.
